<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<title><%= it.school %> (ArborTimetableToPDF)</title>
		<meta charset="utf-8">
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
		<link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.8/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" integrity="sha384-sRIl4kxILFvY47J16cr9ZwB07vP4J8+LH7qKQnuqkuIAvNWLzeN8tE5YBujZqJLB" crossorigin="anonymous">
		<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap-icons@1.11.0/font/bootstrap-icons.css">
		<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.8/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js" integrity="sha384-FKyoEForCGlyvwx9Hj09JcYn3nv7wiPVlz7YYwJrWVcXK/BmnVDxM+D2scQbITxI" crossorigin="anonymous" defer></script>

		<style>
	        .table-bordered th,
	        .table-bordered td {
	            border-width: 4px;
	            border-color: #ccc;
	        }

	        html, body {
	            height: 100%;
	        }

	        body {
	            display: flex;
	            flex-direction: column;
	        }

	        @media print {
	            .no-print {
	                display: none !important;
	            }
	        }

	        [data-bs-toggle="collapse"] {
	            transition: transform 300ms cubic-bezier(0.175, 0.885, 0.32, 1.475);
	        }

	        [data-bs-toggle="collapse"][aria-expanded="true"] {
	            transform: rotate(90deg);
	        }
		</style>
	</head>

	<body class="container-fluid">

		<%~ include('table', it) %>

		<div class="alert alert-dark no-print" role="alert">
			<h3>
				<button class="btn btn-link text-decoration-none text-dark p-0 fs-4" style="line-height: 0;" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#printTips" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="printTips">
					<i class="bi bi-chevron-right"></i>
				</button>
				<span>Tips for the perfect print! üñ®Ô∏è</span>
			</h3>
			<div class="collapse" id="printTips">
				<p>This box of text <strong class="text-danger">won't appear</strong> in your final print, so don't worry about that.</p>
				<hr>
				<ul>
					<li>Want to see the colouring for breaktimes, but it's not showing up when printing? Look for a "<strong>Print backgrounds</strong>" checkbox in your browser's print window.</li>
					<li>Perhaps you want the table to be bigger/smaller or fix some text wrapping issues? If so, look for a "<strong>Scale</strong>" option in your browser's print window! This helps solve some issues where text goes on a new line, or rows appearing on a new page.</li>
					<li>Printing in <strong>landscape</strong> can help a lot, and looks much better in general!</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</div>

	</body>
</html>